Stefan Seip is a professional photographer and astrophotographer, living in Stuttgart. He is the author of several photography books on the sky, the night sky and on astrophotography and travels the globe in search of the locations for his images.

Hohenzollern Castle was first documented in 1267. In 1423 it was completely destroyed after a nine months siege and from 1454 a second and larger castle was constructed.

It fell into ruin towards the end of the 18th century but was rebuilt in its present form, as one of the most impressive neo gothic castles in Germany.

